# We're all chums at Chummy's

35:09.800 --> 35:14.200
# Loyal to the end

35:14.200 --> 35:17.560
# Come here as a stranger

35:17.560 --> 35:22.760
# And you'll go home as a friend

35:22.760 --> 35:26.920
# When you come to Chummy's

35:26.920 --> 35:31.000
# All your dreams come true

35:31.000 --> 35:35.560
# So come, come, come to Chummy's

35:35.560 --> 35:40.040
# We're waiting here for you. #

35:40.040 --> 35:42.920
APPLAUSE

35:47.000 --> 35:49.160
MUSIC PLAYS

35:52.760 --> 35:56.520
LAUGHTER

36:13.800 --> 36:16.240
APPLAUSE

36:23.000 --> 36:24.320
Of course!

36:26.000 --> 36:28.160
Will you excuse me?

36:28.160 --> 36:31.440
Excuse me. Sorry. Sorry.

36:31.440 --> 36:33.680
Sorry. Thank you.

36:33.680 --> 36:36.040
WHISTLING AND APPLAUSE

36:50.200 --> 36:52.080
KNOCKING

36:53.360 --> 36:56.000
Mr Beauchamp, may I have a word?

36:56.000 --> 36:57.360
Er, yeah.

37:01.440 --> 37:04.680
How did you make those
flowers appear?

37:04.680 --> 37:06.800
A magician never tells.

37:06.800 --> 37:09.000
No, of course.

37:09.000 --> 37:10.840
In the radio studio,

37:10.840 --> 37:13.200
after Mrs Chummy's death,

37:13.200 --> 37:16.080
someone made a tape disappear.

37:17.320 --> 37:19.640
And watching you tonight,
I think I know who.

37:25.280 --> 37:28.680
No.
Oh, Mrs Chummy. I...

37:28.680 --> 37:30.920
Just take some deep breaths.
You'll be all right.

37:30.920 --> 37:34.720
There must be a homicidal
maniac about!

37:34.720 --> 37:38.280
You used Mavis' consternation
as a distraction

37:38.280 --> 37:40.360
to take away a vital piece
of evidence.

37:40.360 --> 37:42.000
I don't know what you're
talking about.

37:42.000 --> 37:45.320
And all for a boy named
Billy Fairfield.

37:49.480 --> 37:51.040
I presume he was your brother?

37:52.920 --> 37:57.520
You see, if you translate Fairfield
into French,

37:57.520 --> 37:59.040
it becomes Beauchamp.

38:00.320 --> 38:02.000
And you must have needed
a new name

38:02.000 --> 38:03.440
to come and work here.

38:05.760 --> 38:07.600
Tell me, what's your real name?

38:07.600 --> 38:09.240
Andrew.

38:09.240 --> 38:10.720
Andrew Fairfield.

38:13.360 --> 38:15.200
Tell me about your brother, Andrew.

38:16.480 --> 38:19.000
Billy was kind.

38:19.000 --> 38:21.240
And he was funny.

38:21.240 --> 38:24.480
And people used to say
he was simple.

38:24.480 --> 38:27.880
Slow learning. But I loved him
more than anyone.

38:30.000 --> 38:33.240
We came here as a family,
and I'd never seen him so happy.

38:34.800 --> 38:36.840
But then he wandered off.

38:36.840 --> 38:38.240
And everyone said, "Don't worry,

38:38.240 --> 38:40.240
"this is the safest place
in the world."

38:41.760 --> 38:45.320
I cannot imagine the pain you
and your parents suffered.

38:46.880 --> 38:49.000
They never got over it.

38:49.000 --> 38:51.320
They died last year.
50 years old.

38:52.520 --> 38:54.040
They looked 100.

38:55.200 --> 38:57.640
So now it was up to you to find out
the truth.

38:57.640 --> 39:01.120
I came here to work. But I only
wanted one thing.

39:05.280 --> 39:07.360
I-I wanted to ask you something.

39:07.360 --> 39:08.760
Oh, yes?

39:08.760 --> 39:12.560
Is it true, er, a boy once drowned
in the swimming pool?

39:13.720 --> 39:18.280
Oh, dear. Who's been putting poison
in your delicate little ears?

39:18.280 --> 39:19.760
One of the visitors.

39:19.760 --> 39:22.840
Well, it was a long time ago.

39:22.840 --> 39:26.720
H-How could it happen with so many
people on duty?

39:26.720 --> 39:28.800
Well, Mavis should have been there,

39:28.800 --> 39:32.080
but she'd just met a carpet salesman
from Droitwich.

39:32.080 --> 39:34.040
And I'd had a long day.

39:35.080 --> 39:39.000
But the thing is, he was abnormal.

39:39.000 --> 39:40.720
Mentally defective.

39:40.720 --> 39:43.200
It was a blessing in disguise
for the poor family.

39:44.880 --> 39:47.120
I know she didn't kill him.
But she didn't care.

39:47.120 --> 39:48.400
And that's enough.

39:48.400 --> 39:51.000
So now you had two people to blame.

39:51.000 --> 39:53.240
Oh, cooey!

39:51.000 --> 39:53.240
SHE GIGGLES

39:57.440 --> 40:00.000
You took Mavis' apron

40:00.000 --> 40:02.440
and went to the radio studio
and prepared to kill

40:02.440 --> 40:05.440
two birds with one stone.

40:02.440 --> 40:05.440
SHE CHOKES

40:13.280 --> 40:15.520
And now you want me to tell
the police?

40:15.520 --> 40:18.000
To save Mavis' life?

40:18.000 --> 40:20.120
I want you to save your own soul.

40:22.160 --> 40:23.760
You love your brother,

40:23.760 --> 40:26.000
and if you want to be with him
in heaven...

40:27.280 --> 40:28.920
..you need to do the right thing.

40:30.560 --> 40:33.320
You need to give up all thoughts
of revenge.

40:33.320 --> 40:35.520
No.

40:35.520 --> 40:37.320
I made Billy a promise -

40:37.320 --> 40:41.400
to punish anyone who failed him or
who lied about what happened.

40:41.400 --> 40:42.960
Right, then!

40:42.960 --> 40:47.400
Now we place Uncle Jock into the
cabinet of death!

40:47.400 --> 40:49.000
Are you all right in there,
Uncle Jock?

40:49.000 --> 40:50.600
I think so!

40:50.600 --> 40:53.120
Get on with it?
It's a very tight squeeze.

40:58.280 --> 40:59.600
Stop!

41:01.640 --> 41:03.440
I think you should put down
that sword.

41:03.440 --> 41:06.320
HE WHISPERS: It's OK, Father.
This thing's retractable.

41:06.320 --> 41:08.840
Right, then. Here it goes.

41:08.840 --> 41:10.920
Straight through the heart.

41:13.600 --> 41:15.640
THEY GASP

41:18.280 --> 41:20.000
Are you all right?
I'm fine.

41:20.000 --> 41:21.560
It's not the first time
I've died on stage.

41:21.560 --> 41:23.240
Help! Get me out of here!

41:23.240 --> 41:25.800
Can anyone tell me what's going on?

41:26.760 --> 41:28.320
This young man can.

41:28.320 --> 41:31.040
And I would ask you to listen
to him without prejudice.

41:32.200 --> 41:35.000
BELLS CHIME

41:37.200 --> 41:38.520
Well, well.

41:38.520 --> 41:41.520
The garden's looking rather
splendid, Father.

41:41.520 --> 41:45.000
Well, I think on balance there's
more alive than dead.

41:45.000 --> 41:47.720
But I'll be glad when
Mrs McCarthy returns.

41:47.720 --> 41:49.160
Ah, look who it is!

41:49.160 --> 41:51.040
Sergeant. Father Brown.

41:51.040 --> 41:53.680
Mavis Jug. How nice to see you.

41:53.680 --> 41:55.800
Oh, it's nice just to be out
in the daylight.

41:55.800 --> 41:57.960
I thought I was going to be stuck
in that cell forever.

41:57.960 --> 42:00.000
And yet, here you are.

42:00.000 --> 42:02.240
And I notice...

42:02.240 --> 42:03.720
I know!

42:03.720 --> 42:05.440
It's like a dream come true.

42:05.440 --> 42:06.680
Congratulations.

42:06.680 --> 42:07.920
Hey, how did you manage it?

42:07.920 --> 42:10.040
Well, you know Mrs Chummy didn't
have any children?

42:10.040 --> 42:13.800
It turns out she's left the holiday
camp to her entire staff.

42:13.800 --> 42:17.400
So Griff is going to take over
as head entertainer.

42:17.400 --> 42:21.000
And, oh, Jock is going to carry on
living with us.

42:21.000 --> 42:23.000
But I don't think he's up
to performing any more.

42:23.000 --> 42:25.000
But we'll look after him.

42:25.000 --> 42:26.280
That's very kind.

42:27.280 --> 42:29.480
And I wish you all the best in your
endeavours.

42:29.480 --> 42:30.760
Thank you.

42:30.760 --> 42:33.000
Oh! And we've got a talent show
next week,

42:33.000 --> 42:35.560
so if either of you want to
give us a turn.

42:37.800 --> 42:40.520
Well, I do know one or two
musical songs.

42:40.520 --> 42:41.840
Well, go on, then.

